    "[section:Verse 1]",
    "I was [G]standing by the window",
    "On one [C]cold and cloudy [G]day",
    "And I saw the hearse come rolling",
    "For to [D7]carry my mother a[G]way",
    "",
    "[section:Chorus]",
    "Will the [G]circle be unbroken",
    "By and [C]by, Lord, by and [G]by",
    "There's a better home a-waiting",
    "In the [D7]sky, Lord, in the [G]sky",
    "",
    "[section:Verse 2]",
    "Lord I [G]told the undertaker",
    "Under[C]taker please drive [G]slow",
    "For this body you are hauling",
    "Lord I [D7]hate to see her [G]go",
    "",
    "[section:Chorus]",
    "Will the [G]circle be unbroken",
    "By and [C]by, Lord, by and [G]by",
    "There's a better home a-waiting",
    "In the [D7]sky, Lord, in the [G]sky"
